# ORIG TITLE    Mafia boss hands himself into to Italy police . 
# ORIG CONTENT  ‘‘Enough, I’m tired of running away, better to end it here,’‘ said Italian mafia boss Giuseppe Pesce as he handed himself into police after three years on the run. Pesce, 33, was sentenced to 16 years in prison after a trial held in his absence in May 2012. He had reportedly been feeling isolated after his wife and one of his lieutenants were arrested. 
